PRIMITIVE ID.long-description: Must consist of printable ASCII characters (like ST) and contain a value present in the associated table, which must not be user-defined.

PRIMITIVE IS.long-description: Must consist of printale ASCII characters (like ST) and contain a value present in the associated table, which must be user-defined.

PRIMITIVE NM.long-description: Numeric data written in decimal, the allowable charcters are the ASCII digits, the leading plus and minus sign, and a single decimal point.

PRIMITIVE ST.long-description: Up to 199 printable ASCII characters in the ASCII range 0x20 (32) to 0x7E (126) except the defined delimiter characters.
